      <p>We use Google Fonts to display typography on our website. When you visit our site, your browser may connect to Google's servers to download font files. Google may collect limited technical information as part of this process. For more information, see <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy">Google's Privacy Policy</a>.</p>

      <h2>4. Children's Privacy</h2>

      <p>Our Service is educational in nature and may be used by individuals of all ages. Since we do not collect any personal information, there is no specific data collection from children under 13 (or the applicable age in your jurisdiction).</p>

      <h2>5. Your Rights</h2>

      <p>Since we do not collect personal data, traditional data subject rights (access, rectification, erasure, etc.) do not apply. However, we are committed to transparency and will answer any questions you may have about our privacy practices.</p>

      <h2>6. Security</h2>

      <p>While we do not collect or store personal data, we take the security of our website seriously. Our site is served over HTTPS to ensure secure communication between your browser and our servers.</p>

      <h2>7. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>

      <p>We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last updated" date.</p>

      <p>You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes. Changes to this Privacy Policy are effective when they are posted on this page.</p>

      <h2>8. Open Source Transparency</h2>

      <p>How To Use Internet is an open-source project. You can review our complete source code, including this privacy policy and all website functionality, at our <a href="https://github.com/gmoigneu/howtouseinternet">GitHub repository</a>. This transparency allows you to verify our privacy claims independently.</p>

